oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of Army doctors at Fort Barrancas, Florida
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This photograph was taken at the Post Hospital at Fort Barrancas, Florida in March 1918. Capt. Daniel B. Cliffe was a doctor in Franklin, Tennessee and served in the Medical Reserve Corps. Beginning in August 1917. He served at Ft. Oglethorpe, Georgia, Hattiesburg, Mississippi, Ft. Barrancas, Florida, New Orleans, Louisiana and Tampa, Florida. He received an honorable discharge on February 28, 1919.
